  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple levels of regulation:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Comprehensive legal definitions of money laundering\n- Specific criminal penalties\n- Mandatory reporting requirements for financial institutions\n\n3. Key Regulatory Components\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Enhanced monitoring of high-risk transactions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n\n5. Specific Focus Areas\n- Banking sector regulations\n- Securities markets\n- Cryptocurrency transactions\n- Real estate transactions\n- International wire transfers\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training programs\n- Independent audits\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining economic transparency.",
